 CROSS-SECTION EVALUATION PROCEDURE                               2722 1451
                                                                  2722 1451
 Adopted procedure is based on careful theoretical                2722 1451
 analysis utilizing available experimental data and               2722 1451
 nuclear reaction model calculations.                             2722 1451
                                                                  2722 1451
 Available experimental data were interpreted  using              2722 1451
 nuclear reaction model code EMPIRE-3 by M. Herman                2722 1451
 et al [EMP]. This code integrates into a single                  2722 1451
 system a number of important modules and features:               2722 1451
                                                                  2722 1451
 - Spherical and deformed Optical Model including                 2722 1451
   coupled-channels (ECIS06 by J. Raynal)                         2722 1451
 - Hauser-Feshbach statistical model including                    2722 1451
   HRTW width fluctuation correction                              2722 1451
 - Quantum-mechanical MSD TUL model (codes ORION &                2722 1451
   TRISTAN by H. Lenske), and MSC NVWY model                      2722 1451
 - Exciton model with angular momentum coupling                   2722 1451
   (code DEGAS by E. Betak and P. Oblozinsky) that                2722 1451
   represents a good approximation to the DSD model               2722 1451
 - Exciton model with Iwamoto-Harada cluster                      2722 1451
   emission and Kalbach systematic angular distr.                 2722 1451
   (code PCROSS by R.Capote et al)                                2722 1451
 - Complete gamma-ray cascade after emission of                   2722 1451
   each particle, including realistic treatment of                2722 1451
   discrete transitions                                           2722 1451
 - Access to OM segment of the RIPL library [RIPL]                2722 1451
 - Built-in input parameter files, such as masses,                2722 1451
   level density, discrete levels, fission barriers               2722 1451
   and gamma strength functions based on the RIPL                 2722 1451
   library [RIPL]                                                 2722 1451
 - Automatic retrieval of experimental data from the              2722 1451
   EXFOR/CSISRS library                                           2722 1451
 - ENDF-6 formatting (code EMPEND by A. Trkov)                    2722 1451
   coupled to graphical presentation capabilities                 2722 1451
   (code ZVView by V. Zerkin) through the chain of                2722 1451
   PrePro codes by R. Cullen                                      2722 1451
 - Checking codes (CHECKR, FIZCON, PSYCHE)                        2722 1451
 - Support for NJOY                                               2722 1451
